[{"location":"#BoxCoxTransformations.jl","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","text":"Modules = [BoxCoxTransformations]","category":"page"},{"location":"#Base.empty!-Tuple{BoxCoxTransformations.PowerTransformation}","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"Base.empty!","text":"empty!(bc::PowerTransformation)\n\nRemove data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#BoxCoxTransformations.transform-Tuple{BoxCoxTransformation}","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"BoxCoxTransformations.transform","text":"transform(bc::BoxCoxTransformation; α = 0, scaled = false)\ntransform(bc::BoxCoxTransformation, λ::Real; α = 0, scaled = false)\n\nReturns transformed data for optimal λ as specified in bc or for a particular λ, if specified.\n\nKeyword arguments:\n\nα: added to all values in 𝐱 before transformation. Default = 0.\nscaled: scale transformation results.  Default = false.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#StatsAPI.confint-Tuple{BoxCoxTransformation}","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"StatsAPI.confint","text":"confint(bc::BoxCoxTransformation; level=0.95)\n\nReturns confidence interval for the estimated maximum power parameter λ of a given BoxCoxTransformation.\n\nNote: The confidence interval is the range of λs for which the log-likelihood(λ) >= loglikelihood(λ_max) - 0.5 * quantile(Chisq(1), level)\n\nReference: Linear Models With R by Julian Faraway Section 7.1.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#StatsAPI.fit-Tuple{Type{BoxCoxTransformation}, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"StatsAPI.fit","text":"fit(::BoxCoxTransformation, 𝐱::Vector{<:Real};\n\t\tinterval = (-2.0, 2.0),method = :geomean, kwargs...)\n\nFit box cox transformation to data.\n\nPower parameter, λ, is determined from 𝐱 using a log-likelihood estimator.\n\nKeyword arguments:\n\nmethod: for the cacluation of the log-likelihood\n\n- :geomean => -N / 2.0 * log(2 * π * σ² / gm ^ (2 * (λ - 1)) + 1)\n- :normal => -N / 2.0 * log(σ²) + (λ - 1) * sum(log.(𝐱))\n\nany other keyword arguments accepted by Optim.optimize function e.g. abs_tol\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#StatsAPI.loglikelihood-Tuple{BoxCoxTransformation}","page":"BoxCoxTransformations.jl","title":"StatsAPI.loglikelihood","text":"loglikelihood(bc::BoxCoxTransformation)\nloglikelihood(bc::BoxCoxTransformation, λ::Real)\n\nReturns log likelihood for optimal λ as specified in bc or for a particular λ, if specified.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
